  <refnamediv>
    <refname>&dhpackage;</refname>

    <refpurpose>manage encrypted block devices</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      <command>&dhpackage;</command>
      <arg choice="opt" rep="repeat"><replaceable>OPTION</replaceable></arg>
      <arg choice="req"><replaceable>action</replaceable></arg>
      <arg choice="req"><replaceable>name</replaceable></arg>
      <arg choice="opt"><replaceable>device</replaceable></arg>
    </cmdsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsect1>
    <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
    <para><command>&dhpackage;</command> provides a command-line interface
      for configuring encrypted block devices. Typically, a filesystem is
      run overtop of this device to create an encrypted filesystem.</para>
    <para>This facility is supported in kernels newer than 2.6.4 and is
      called dm-crypt. It is backwards compatible with the old
      cryptoloop system.</para>
  </refsect1>
  <refsect1>
    <title>OPTIONS</title>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-v</option>, <option>--verbose</option>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Shows more detailed error messages.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>
<option>-c</option> <replaceable>STRING</replaceable>, <option>--cipher=</option><replaceable>STRING</replaceable>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>The cipher used to encrypt the disk (see
                <filename>/proc/crypto</filename>)
                (default: <quote>aes</quote>).</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-h</option> <replaceable>STRING</replaceable>, <option>--hash=</option><replaceable>STRING</replaceable>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>The hash used to create the encryption key from
                the passphrase (default: <quote>ripemd160</quote>).</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-y</option>, <option>--verify-passphrase</option>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Verifies the passphrase by asking for it twice.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-d</option> <replaceable>STRING</replaceable>, <option>--key-file=</option><replaceable>STRING</replaceable>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Read the raw key data from a file (can be
          <filename>/dev/random</filename>). The key data will not
          be hashed, ie. the <option>-h</option> option will be ignored.
          This implies that <option>-d</option>
          <literal>/dev/stdin</literal> is only the same as running
          <literal>cryptsetup</literal> without the <option>-d</option> option when
          <option>-h</option> <literal>plain</literal> is used.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-s</option> <replaceable>BITS</replaceable>, <option>--key-size=</option><replaceable>BITS</replaceable>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>The size of the encryption key (default: 256).</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-b</option> <replaceable>SECTORS</replaceable>, <option>--size=</option><replaceable>SECTORS</replaceable>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>The size of the device.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-o</option> <replaceable>SECTORS</replaceable>, <option>--offset=</option><replaceable>SECTORS</replaceable>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>The start offset in the backend device.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-p</option> <replaceable>SECTORS</replaceable>, <option>--skip=</option><replaceable>SECTORS</replaceable>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>How many sectors of the encrypted data to skip
                at the beginning.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-r</option>, <option>--readonly</option>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Create a readonly mapping.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-?</option>, <option>--help</option>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Show a help message.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>--usage</option>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Display brief usage.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsect1>
  <refsect1>
    <title>ARGUMENTS</title>
    <para><replaceable>action</replaceable> is one of:</para>
    <blockquote>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><literal>create</literal></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>create device</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><literal>remove</literal></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>remove device</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><literal>reload</literal></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>modify active device</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><literal>resize</literal></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>resize active device</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><literal>status</literal></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>show device status</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
    </blockquote>
    <para><replaceable>name</replaceable> is the device to create under
    /dev/mapper.</para>
    <para><replaceable>device</replaceable> is the encrypted device.</para>
  </refsect1>
  <refsect1>
    <title>EXAMPLES</title>
    <programlisting>cryptsetup create crypted\-hda1 /dev/hda1</>
    <programlisting>openssl enc \-d \-aes\-256\-ecb \-in crypt.key | \\
       cryptsetup \-c twofish \-h sha512 create _dev_hda1 /dev/hda1</>
    <programlisting>cryptsetup remove crypted\-hda1</>
  </refsect1>
